@startuml data-pipeline
!theme plain
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title NestJS Data Pipeline - Hotel Management Server

actor "Client\n(Web/Mobile)" as Client
participant "main.ts\n(Entry Point)" as Main
participant "AllExceptionsFilter" as Filter
participant "JwtAuthGuard\n(Global)" as AuthGuard
participant "TransformInterceptor\n(Global)" as Interceptor
participant "ValidationPipe\n(Global)" as Pipe
participant "Controller\n(e.g., RoomsController)" as Controller
participant "Service\n(e.g., RoomsService)" as Service
participant "Repository" as Repository
database "Database\n(MySQL)" as DB

== Request Flow ==

Client -> Main : HTTP Request (API Route)
activate Main

Main -> AuthGuard : 1. Authentication Check
activate AuthGuard
AuthGuard --> Main : Allow / Deny
deactivate AuthGuard
note right of AuthGuard: Validates JWT tokens for protected routes

Main -> Interceptor : 2. Intercept Request
activate Interceptor
Interceptor --> Main : Continue
deactivate Interceptor
note right of Interceptor: Can modify request or handle caching

Main -> Pipe : 3. Validate & Transform Payload
activate Pipe
Pipe --> Main : Transformed DTO
deactivate Pipe
note right of Pipe: Uses class-validator to validate body/query/params

Main -> Controller : 4. Route to Handler
activate Controller

Controller -> Service : 5. Execute Business Logic
activate Service

Service -> Repository : 6. Data Access
activate Repository

Repository -> DB : 7. SQL Query
activate DB
DB --> Repository : Result Set
deactivate DB

Repository --> Service : Entities
deactivate Repository

Service --> Controller : Processed Data
deactivate Service

Controller --> Main : Response Object
deactivate Controller

== Response Flow ==

Main -> Interceptor : 8. Intercept Response
activate Interceptor
Interceptor --> Main : Transformed Response (e.g. Wrap in { data: ... })
deactivate Interceptor
note right of Interceptor: Standardizes API response format

Main -> Client : 9. HTTP Response
deactivate Main

== Error Handling (Anywhere in Pipeline) ==
note over Main, Repository: If an exception is thrown at any point

Filter -> Client : Intercept Exception & Format Error Response
note right of Filter: Transforms exceptions into standard API error format
@enduml
